headline: For CEOs and Bankers, the Trump Euphoria Is Fading Fast
summary: It took less than a month for the second Trump administration to cool the enthusiasm of chief executives and dealmakers.  Consumer sentiment is down and inflation expectations are rising, driven in part by worries about the impact of a threatened trade war.  A Justice Department that was expected to wave through acquisitions instead sued to block a big technology merger.
